Package: proxmox-mlx5-sriov
Version: @VERSION@
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: schlarpc <schlarpc@gmail.com>
Depends: pve-manager (>= 8.0.0), iproute2, ethtool
Description: Mellanox SR-IOV VF provisioning for Proxmox VE
 Creates SR-IOV virtual functions on a Mellanox ConnectX NIC (switchdev mode
 with deterministic per-VF MACs) and registers them as Proxmox PCI resource
 mappings. The work is split across two correctly-ordered systemd template
 units so the VF/representor setup runs before networking while the pvesh
 mapping sync runs after pmxcfs is available.
 .
 Per-PF instances are enabled as mlx5-sriov-vfs@<interface>.service.
 Configuration is optional: the PF comes from the instance name, the VF count
 and MAC prefix are derived, and per-PF overrides may be dropped in
 /etc/default/mlx5-sriov.d/.
